===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|capital}}, a {{bor|en|la|capitālis||of the head|nocap=1}}, in sense “head of [[cattle]]”, from {{m|la|caput||head}} (English {{m|en|cap}}). Use in trade and finance originated in Medieval economies when a common but expensive transaction involved trading heads of cattle.

Compare {{doublet|chattel|lang=en|notext=1}} and {{m|en|kith and kine||all one’s possessions}}, which also use “cow” to mean “property”.

